<br>
Had a 60 war as the MA, with the only other melees being myself(54 pally) and a 54 warrior. Casters were a 51 wiz, 60 mage(air pet), 55 mage(rage of zomm), 56 mage(air pet), 60 epic shaman, 51 druid, 58 cleric, 50 cleric, and a 52 enchanter. Did standard raid buffs(cleric buffs, symbols for tanks, shammy did Khura's focusing, etc.) The enchanter put Rune V on all the tanks as an added security. We pulled him to zone wall near the log at 1500, -800 in Nek. Shaman malosi'd, enchanter tashed, shaman, druid, and enchanter dotted him.  The warrior said that he wasn't hitting him for any more than 180, doubles. Casters nuked at 50. Went down really easy. I don't even think the clerics had to heal more than once, if even that. The MA was at 90% life when he went down, and I didn't see him get healed any. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulourrenytblytr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lourre Nytblytr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/19/02 7:25:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3662.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The lowdown on Kirak Vil.</span><hr size=1> The key to Kirak seems to be getting the Shammy slow and stacking DoTs to keep his insane regen down.  Then send in a wave of tanks to beat him down.  We did him with less than 2 groups of 50-55s.<br>
